      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, i feel like you're missing the point of the character. it's not about finding a \"purpose\" or a \"connection\"... it's about the relief of it being over. like, if you knew you were just a broken file, wouldn't you want the system to just fix it by deleting it? it seems so much more logical to just let it go than to keep struggling through the glitches. why is it so hard to just accept that some things are meant to end?",
